","Beverston, Gloucestershire, England":"Beverston, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Margery","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual medieval vernacular form of   Margaret   (now also commonly spelled   Marjorie  ). This form of the name is preserved in the nursery rhyme ‘See-saw, Margery Daw’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":11,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":20,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Margery DeQuarmby was born on 3 November 1203, in Charlton, Somerset, England, her father, Reginald  Fits Peter Herbert Jones of Llanarth and Treowen, was 38 and her mother, Alis verch Bleddyn Broadspear, was 25. She married Sir William FitzAdam II in 1220, in Somerset, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died on 2 November 1247, in Tutbury, Staffordshire, England, at the age of 43."},"et":{"3 November 1203–2 November 1247":"3. november 1203–2. november 1247","1203–1247":"1203–1247","1195–1252":"1195–1252","1220–1282":"1220–1282","1220–1300":"1220–1300","1223–1300":"1223–1300","1165–1206":"1165–1206","1178–Female":"1178–Surnud","1220":"1220","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1195":"1195","1282":